    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Answered on SO as well. \nThe reshape function takes the new shape as a tuple rather than as multiple arguments. Reshape is actually implemented in Series and will return an ndarray:\n\nIn [11]: a\nOut[11]: \n0    1\n1    2\n2    3\n3    4\n\nIn [12]: a.reshape((2, 2))\nOut[12]: \narray([[1, 2],\n       [3, 4]])\n"
